# Item Suggestions — Implementation Plan

## Feature Summary

The item name input in additionalLoggingDetails gains a dropdown activated by a caret
button. The dropdown shows up to 25 ranked items (7 visible, scrollable) based on a
frequency-weighted algorithm favoring recent usage. Typing in the field filters the list.

---

## Algorithm

### Scoring

One query fetches all calLog entries from the last 30 days. Three overlapping time
windows are counted per unique non-empty item name (case-insensitive grouping):

    freq3  = count of appearances in last 3 days
    freq7  = count of appearances in last 7 days
    freq30 = count of appearances in last 30 days

    presence = (freq3 > 0 ? 1 : 0)
             + (freq7 > 0 ? 1 : 0)
             + (freq30 > 0 ? 1 : 0)

    score = (freq3 × 5) + (freq7 × 3) + (freq30 × 1) + (presence × 4)

Windows overlap intentionally — an item logged yesterday scores in all three buckets.
The multipliers (5 / 3 / 1 / 4) are tunable constants defined in the use-case file.

### Ranking

1. Sort all scored items descending by score.
2. Take the top 25.
3. If fewer than 25, fill remaining slots with the most recently logged unique names
   not already in the list (one entry each, ordered by recency).
4. No item appears more than once.

### Case Handling

- Group by name.toLowerCase() when counting.
- Display the most recently used casing (the casing from the newest calLog row for
  that normalized name).

