## Performance Strategy: In-Memory Cache with Dirty Flag

No extra IndexedDB table. Data volume is ~150-300 rows for 30 days. A single indexed
range query on createdOn takes <20ms even on low-end phones. The dropdown opens on an
explicit user tap, so the compute is imperceptible.

    ┌──────────────┐   first open / dirty    ┌───────────────────┐
    │   Dropdown   │ ──────────────────────▶  │  getLastNDays(30) │
    │   requests   │                          │  compute scores   │
    │   top items  │ ◀──────────────────────  │  cache result     │
    └──────────────┘    return cached list     └───────────────────┘

- Compute on first dropdown open. Store the ranked list in a module-level variable.
- Set a dirty flag after any logCalEntry, deleteLogEntry, or updateLogEntry completes.
- Next dropdown open checks the flag: dirty → recompute; clean → return cached list.
- No DB migration. No extra table. No async sync.

### Invalidation Hook

Export a simple invalidate function from the use-case file. Call it from logCalEntry,
deleteLogEntry, and updateLogEntry after their await completes.

