## New Repository Method

CalLogRepository.getLastNDays(n):

    async getLastNDays(n) {
      const now = new Date();
      const start = new Date(
        now.getFullYear(), now.getMonth(), now.getDate() - n
      ).toISOString();
      return db
        .table("calLog")
        .where("createdOn")
        .above(start)
        .toArray();
    }

Single indexed range scan. Returns all fields (id, calories, name, description,
createdOn, updatedOn). The use-case only reads name and createdOn.

