## UI Behavior

### Caret Button

- Small down-caret icon (▾ character or SVG) appended inside or after the name input.
- Touch target: 44×44 CSS pixels minimum.
- Tapping the caret calls getTopItems() and opens the dropdown.
- If the dropdown is already open, tapping the caret closes it.

### Dropdown List

- A ul element positioned below the name input.
- Max 7 visible items (item height × 7 = list max-height), overflow-y: auto for
  scrolling.
- Each li shows the item name. Tap selects: sets nameInput.value and closes dropdown.
- :active state for tap feedback.

### Typing Filter

- While dropdown is open and user types in nameInput, filter the cached list by
  case-insensitive prefix match and re-render visible items.
- If filter produces 0 matches, show "No matches" disabled item.
- If dropdown is closed and user types, do NOT auto-open. Only the caret opens it.

### Closing

- Tap outside the dropdown or the name input → close.
- Escape key → close.
- Selecting an item → close.

### Accessibility

- Dropdown gets role="listbox", items get role="option".
- Caret button gets aria-label="Show recent items", aria-expanded="true/false".
- Arrow keys navigate the list, Enter selects.

